const pageContent = "<div id=\"T4281391803\" page-url=\"menu_web\" class=\"page pinned pinned-top fixed\"><a id=\"menu_web\"></a><div class=\"page-layout\"><div class=\"page-content\"><bodycopy style=\"--fit-height: 10px; --resize-parent-width: 100%;\"><header class=\"header-web\" role=\"banner\">\n  <br>\n  <div class=\"header-web__inner\">\n    <a class=\"header-web__brand\" href=\"/\">THERE &amp; BACK AGAIN</a>\n\n    <nav aria-label=\"Primary\" class=\"header-web__nav\">\n      <a class=\"header-web__link\" href=\"/chronicles/\">CHRONICLES</a>\n      <a class=\"header-web__link\" href=\"/by-region/\">BY REGION</a>\n      <a class=\"header-web__link\" href=\"/about-the-traveller/\">THE TRAVELLER</a>\n    </nav>\n  </div>\n  <br>\n</header>\n\n<hr class=\"header-rule\"></bodycopy></div></div></div><div style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\" class=\"pages\"><div id=\"J0226862870\" page-url=\"about-the-traveller\" class=\"page\"><a id=\"about-the-traveller\"></a><div class=\"page-layout\"><div class=\"page-content\"><bodycopy style=\"--fit-height: 10px; --resize-parent-width: 100%;\"><div class=\"page-header\">\n<section class=\"hero\">\n  <div class=\"hero-ornament\">Of the traveller</div>\n  <h1 class=\"hero-title\">A Traveller of<br><em>Considerable</em><br>Appetite</h1>\n  <p class=\"hero-subtitle\">There is little that needs to be said of the traveller, save that they are fond of good food, long roads, and returning home with more stories than they set out with.</p>\n</section>\n\n<div class=\"divider\"></div>\n\n<div class=\"content\">\n\n  <div class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"chapter-label\">I. Of their nature</div>\n    <div class=\"prose\">\n      <p>The <a href=\"/front-page/\">traveller</a> is, by disposition, a creature of the road. Not by restlessness — they are equally fond of the armchair, the long meal, the second helping — but by a conviction, held quietly and without apology, that the world is <em>larger and stranger and more generous</em> than any single life spent in one place could account for.</p>\n      <p>They travel alone. Not from misanthropy — they have been known to linger over a shared bottle until the proprietor begins stacking chairs — but because solo travel demands a particular quality of attention. When there is no companion to consult, the traveller must look harder, listen more carefully, and make peace with being lost in a foreign city at dusk with only their wits and a vague memory of where they ate lunch.</p>\n      <p>They consider this an education.</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <blockquote>\n    <p>\"The wise traveller knows two things above all others: that the road is long, and that it is best faced on a full stomach.\"</p>\n  </blockquote>\n\n  <div class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"chapter-label\">II. Of their manner of travel</div>\n    <div class=\"traits\">\n      <div class=\"trait\">\n        <div class=\"trait-label\">Pace</div>\n        <div class=\"trait-value\">Slow. The traveller does not collect cities. They inhabit them.</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"trait\">\n        <div class=\"trait-label\">Philosophy</div>\n        <div class=\"trait-value\">One great meal is worth three monuments.</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"trait\">\n        <div class=\"trait-label\">Transport</div>\n        <div class=\"trait-value\">Train where possible. The window seat is non-negotiable.</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"trait\">\n        <div class=\"trait-label\">Luggage</div>\n        <div class=\"trait-value\">Carry-on only. Heavy bags are for those who do not trust the road.</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"trait\">\n        <div class=\"trait-label\">Accommodation</div>\n        <div class=\"trait-value\">Whatever puts them in the right neighbourhood. Luxury is optional. Location is not.</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"trait\">\n        <div class=\"trait-label\">Budget</div>\n        <div class=\"trait-value\">Honest. The numbers in these chronicles are real.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"chapter-label\">III. Of these chronicles</div>\n    <div class=\"prose\">\n      <p>This blog was begun for a simple reason: the traveller could not find the kind of travel writing they actually wanted to read. Everything was either <em>beautiful and useless</em> — lyrical prose that told you nothing about where to eat or how to get there — or useful and joyless, a spreadsheet dressed as a story.</p>\n      <p>There and Back Again is an attempt at both at once. The narrative sections are written in earnest — no irony, no winking at the reader, no apology for the register. The practical sections are written with equal seriousness. A budget is not beneath the dignity of good prose. A restaurant recommendation is not incompatible with fine writing.</p>\n      <p>The traveller has been to many places and intends to go to many more. Australia is home — which means the road is always long before it even begins, and the return is always sweeter for it.</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"chapter-label\">IV. Lands visited</div>\n    <div class=\"prose\">\n      <p>The map grows slowly, as all good maps do.</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"countries\">\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">Italy</span>\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">Morocco</span>\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">Japan</span>\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">Spain</span>\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">France</span>\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">Portugal</span>\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">Greece</span>\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">Turkey</span>\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">Vietnam</span>\n      <span class=\"country-tag\">Thailand</span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"cta-strip\">\n  <p>\"The road goes ever on. Begin here.\"</p>\n  <a class=\"cta-link\" href=\"/chronicles/\">Read the chronicles →</a>\n</div></div></bodycopy></div></div></div></div>";
